{
  "_comment": [
    "Recommended permissions for a project hosting the sigma-workbook-conventions skill.",
    "Merge the `allow` and `ask` arrays below into your project's `.claude/settings.json`",
    "under `permissions`. With these rules, discovery and inspection operations",
    "(scripts/api/*, mcp-search.sh, mcp-describe.sh, find-file-by-urlid.sh, ...) run",
    "without approval prompts. Authoring/publishing (curl POST/PUT to /v2/workbooks)",
    "still prompts — by design — since those are state-changing.",
    "",
    "Companion rule the skill documents in its 'Bash invocation hygiene' section:",
    "  invoke scripts BARE (no `cd <repo> &&` prefix). The `Bash(cd * && ...)`",
    "  entries below are a safety net in case an agent ignores that rule.",
    "",
    "Anything in `ask` MUST stay prompting — destructive ops with no undo."
  ],
  "permissions": {
    "allow": [
      "Bash(scripts/api/*)",
      "Bash(bash scripts/api/*)",
      "Bash(cd * && scripts/api/*)",
      "Bash(cd * && python3 scripts/*)",
      "Bash(python3 scripts/sigma-resolve.py:*)",
      "Bash(python3 scripts/validate-spec.py:*)",
      "Bash(bash scripts/refresh-vendor.sh:*)",
      "Bash(eval \"$(scripts/load-env.sh)\")",
      "Bash(eval \"$(*get-token.sh)\")",
      "Bash(bash *get-token.sh)",
      "Bash(export SIGMA_API_TOKEN=*)",
      "Bash(SIGMA_API_TOKEN=*)",
      "Bash(curl * $SIGMA_BASE_URL/v2/dataModels/*)",
      "Bash(curl * $SIGMA_BASE_URL/v2/workbooks/*)",
      "Bash(curl * $SIGMA_BASE_URL/v2/files*)",
      "Bash(curl * $SIGMA_BASE_URL/v2/connections*)",
      "Bash(curl * $SIGMA_BASE_URL/v2/members*)",
      "Bash(curl * $SIGMA_BASE_URL/mcp/v2*)",
      "Bash(cd *)",
      "Bash(echo *)",
      "Bash(ls:*)",
      "Bash(mkdir:*)",
      "Bash(cat:*)",
      "Bash(head:*)",
      "Bash(tail:*)",
      "Bash(jq:*)",
      "Bash(cp:*)",
      "Bash(find:*)",
      "Bash(grep:*)",
      "Bash(git clone:*)",
      "Bash(git status:*)",
      "Bash(git diff:*)",
      "Bash(git log:*)",
      "Bash(python3 -c:*)"
    ],
    "ask": [
      "Bash(curl * -X DELETE *)"
    ]
  }
}
